cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with rerouting flows in a network.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for computing maximum reroutable flows.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper involves combinatorial algorithms and half-integral flows.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the max flow/min cut gap and approximation ratios.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper proves NP-hardness results for certain variants of the reroutable flow problem.
